            <div class="article-faq">
                <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Is it safe to upload confidential documents to online PDF tools?</summary>
                    <p>It depends entirely on the specific tool and its data handling practices. Tools with explicit, verifiable data deletion policies, no AI training on user data, and encryption in transit and at rest provide a reasonable level of security for most professional documents. For documents subject to attorney-client privilege, HIPAA, or classified status, additional verification is required.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Can AI tools use my uploaded documents to train their models?</summary>
                    <p>Some can, if their terms of service permit it. This is more common with free consumer tools. Always check the terms of service for language about "service improvement," "model training," or "content use." PdfToolStack explicitly does not train on user documents under any circumstances.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>What is the difference between GDPR-compliant and HIPAA-compliant tools?</summary>
                    <p>GDPR (EU) and HIPAA (US healthcare) are different regulatory frameworks with different requirements. GDPR compliance means the tool handles personal data according to EU privacy law. HIPAA compliance means the tool has signed a Business Associate Agreement and meets healthcare data standards. A tool can be GDPR compliant without being HIPAA compliant, and vice versa. Most consumer PDF tools are neither.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>How long does PdfToolStack store uploaded files?</summary>
                    <p>All uploaded files are automatically and permanently deleted within 1 hour of processing. This applies to both the input file and any output files. Files are not archived, backed up with your content, or retained for any purpose beyond the immediate processing task.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>Can I use PdfToolStack for HIPAA-covered documents?</summary>
                    <p>PdfToolStack is not currently a HIPAA-covered entity and has not signed Business Associate Agreements. Healthcare professionals handling PHI (Protected Health Information) should use a dedicated HIPAA-compliant document management solution for covered transactions. Non-clinical documents that don't contain PHI can generally be processed with standard tools.</p>
                </details>

                <details class="article-faq-item">
                    <summary>What should I do if I accidentally uploaded a sensitive document?</summary>
                    <p>PdfToolStack automatically deletes all files within 1 hour. If you're concerned, you can contact us at admin@pdftoolstack.com and we will confirm deletion. For future documents, consider using the <a href="/redact-pdf">Redact PDF tool</a> to remove sensitive identifiers before uploading to any online service.</p>
                </details>
            </div>

